  "text": ", where i = 0, 2, 3, 4. It is easy to observe that the degree of h 0 appearing in the 6-point CHY form can be at most 4, resulting in the possible reduction matrices being the following, The canonical coefficients forming the vector A σ i are obtained by solving the local duality constraints and the intersection number constraint for the ideal {h 1 , h 2 , h 3 , h 0 }, where h 0 = σ i . Such cases are studied in detail in [CITATION_1] and the analytical solutions can be directly read off from the tableaux representations as the following, = 0, which is equivalent to the scattering equations.",
